    <string name="help_content">How to use:\n\n• Basic operations: +, -, *, /\n• Parentheses are supported: (2+3)*4\n• Percent is binary: x % y = y*x/100. Example: 50%200 = 100\n• Factorial works only for whole n ≥ 0, and up to 20!\n• Trigonometry: sin(x), cos(x), tan(x). Switch DEG/RAD for angle units\n• Logarithms: ln(x), log10(x), only for x > 0\n• Square root: sqrt(x) or √x, only for x ≥ 0\n• Nth root button (ⁿ√x) inserts ^(1/. Example: 27^(1/3) = 3\n• Constants: π = 3.1415926536, e = 2.7182818285\n• Decimal point and comma are both accepted; comma is normalized to dot\n\nExamples:\n• sin(90) in DEG = 1\n• ln(2.7182818285) = 1\n• log10(100) = 2\n• 5! = 120</string>
